main event: On 8th August 1958, in Shrewsbury, New Jersey, a stationary white object at an estimated altitude of 10,000-15,000 ft was observed, and then the light went out after a 5-minute observation.
interesting points: The object was described as white, stationary, and then the light went out.
The observation was classified as ground-visual.
Weather conditions were reported as clear with various wind speeds at different altitudes.
The report concludes that there was insufficient data to make a conclusion.
There were no photographs included in the report.
sighted object: stationary white object in the sky
witnesses: Electronics Engineer from Ft. Monmouth, NJ
